  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Borusan Group is a major Turkish company involved in steel and pipe production, distribution of automobiles and heavy construction equipment, a logistics company and in new technologies. The proposed project consists of:
-  restructuring the balance sheet; 
      -  implementing a number of corporate initiatives to improve productivity; and 
      -  strengthening corporate governance.  

The objective is to improve the companys overall operational and financial performance. Borusan Group is organized into five divisions: 
-  Steel Pipe Division:
 comprising three companies which together represent one of the top five pipe manufacturers in Europe; 

-  Distribution Division:
 comprising the sales and support for Caterpillar construction and earth moving equipment and power systems and also BMW and Land Rover passenger vehicles; 

-  Flat Steel Division:
 which includes Bor&#xE7;elik, an IFC client, with cold-rolling steel operations; 

-Logistics Division:
which provides logistics, domestic and international transport, port, warehousing and other services to third parties; and,

-  Technology Division:
 offering LAN, alternative telecom and other IT services and taking partnerships in high growth IT and telecom companies.</narrative>
  </description>
